@startuml signature
!include ../_includes/style.iuml
!include ../_includes/legend.iuml

' DRY composer — the class definitions live in
' _includes/classes/routing-types.iuml. Any other diagram that needs
' to reference these shapes (`Signature`, `BehavioralSignature`, …)
' should `!include` the SAME partial — never redeclare.

!include ../_includes/classes/routing-types.iuml

title BehavioralSignature — shape on disk (`.ts/<file>.json`)

' Persistence side — kept inline because it's diagram-specific (a
' different composer might show signatureStore behaviour without the
' on-disk database).
package "src/main/modelhub/routing/" <<Folder>> {
  component "signatureStore.ts\nloadSignature() / writeSignature()" as STORE
}
database ".ts/<modelfile>.json\n(per-model sidecar)" as DISK

Signature *-- StructuralSignature
Signature *-- BehavioralSignature
Signature *-- QcmReliability
BehavioralSignature *-- "many" DiagnosticRunEntry
STORE ..> Signature : serialise / parse
STORE -- DISK : JSON

note right of BehavioralSignature::scores_per_leaf
  Beta-Laplace `(1+passes)/(2+asked)` ∈ (0, 1].
  3/3 ⇒ 0.80, never 1.0 in Phase A.
  Coexists with `scores_per_axis` (R5 fallback).
end note

note right of BehavioralSignature::topic_coverage_per_leaf
  DCC §4 carve-out. 32 cosines against
  the SAME shared anchors used by routing —
  same index space as `scores_per_leaf`.
  Additional evidence, never replacement.
end note

note bottom of QcmReliability
  SPEC §6bis: QCM aptitude is a
  judge-candidacy signal, never
  a competence signal for routing.
end note

@enduml
